  "name": "One Body, Two Minds",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/affliction_21.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 15th level, once per day, you can improve the effectiveness of a single spell by having your possessing spirit channel that spell. The spell acts as though it were affected by both the @Compendium[pf1.feats.2YuxcUNFMPNBpekG]{Silent Spell}&nbsp;and @Compendium[pf1.feats.jVFjMIyQD6TOAsmj]{Still Spell}&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/metamagic-feats\">metamagic feats</a>. If the spell chosen is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Magic-Descriptor-Mind-Affecting\">mind-affecting</a>&nbsp;spell, it also benefits from the @Compendium[pf1.feats.btXWioB3SKJv8YEG]{Extend Spell}&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/metamagic-feats\">metamagic feat</a>. This ability does not use up a spell slot higher than the level of the base spell, nor does it increase the level of the base spell.</p>",
